s + Athina Mari)\\\\n\\\\n### Key Stops & Dates (from Markdown + XLSX)\\\\n\\\\n**Cairo (arrival stopover)** — Aug 3–5, 2 nights, Eileen Hotel ($102). Fly in Aug 3 (ATH→CAI, Aege… (7799 chars total)\\\"\\n\\nALREADY EXECUTED (do not repeat any of these statements — write only what comes NEXT):\\n// setSessionMeta is fire-and-forget — name the session, set activity, and start the work all in one statement.\\nsetSessionMeta({ title: 'Tanzania trip organization', slug: 'tanzania-trip' });\\nsetActivity('Reading your Tanzania materials');\\n// Delegate the image and files in parallel — vision for the photo, files for the notes, spreadsheet, and PDF.\\nconst [photoResult, filesResult] = await Promise.all([\\n  delegate('system-vision', 'vision', {\\n    query: 'Describe this photo in detail — where it was taken, what it shows, any notable features or atmosphere.',\\n    attachmentIds: ['6a5d9f14-644b-4698-a341-109093144d31'],\\n  }),\\n  delegate('system-files', 'dispatch', {\\n    query: 'Summarize these three documents briefly but concretely. For the markdown notes: list the key stops/destinations, dates if any, and any practical notes. For the spreadsheet: list every sheet name and a summary of what each contains (column names and a rough row count). For the PDF (park fees): extract the fee categories, amounts, and any important rules or notes. Give me enough specifics that I can speak about each one credibly.',\\n    attachmentIds: [\\n      '0d232466-6bcb-4b15-ab99-604b1bb01526',\\n      '2028d990-7e6a-4ad1-9b37-60ed5ac27a25',\\n      '33968e28-329f-49da-8d2e-3d516a0e3b40',\\n    ],\\n  }),\\n]) as [string, string];\",\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/sessions/f22a48fc-367c-410b-8555-99efa1a74168/snapshot.json:48:      \"content\": \"VARIABLES\\n\\nSCOPE (already declared — do not redeclare): photoResult, filesResult\\n\\nALREADY EXECUTED (do not repeat any of these statements — write only what comes NEXT):\\n// setSessionMeta is fire-and-forget — name the session, set activity, and start the work all in one statement.\\nsetSessionMeta({ title: 'Tanzania trip organization', slug: 'tanzania-trip' });\\nsetActivity('Reading your Tanzania materials');\\n// Delegate the image and files in parallel — vision for the photo, files for the notes, spreadsheet, and PDF.\\nconst [photoResult, filesResult] = await Promise.all([\\n  delegate('system-vision', 'vision', {\\n    query: 'Describe this photo in detail — where it was taken, what it shows, any notable features or atmosphere.',\\n    attachmentIds: ['6a5d9f14-644b-4698-a341-109093144d31'],\\n  }),\\n  delegate('system-files', 'dispatch', {\\n    query: 'Summarize these three documents briefly but concretely. For the markdown notes: list the key stops/destinations, dates if any, and any practical notes. For the spreadsheet: list every sheet name and a summary of what each contains (column names and a rough row count). For the PDF (park fees): extract the fee categories, amounts, and any important rules or notes. Give me enough specifics that I can speak about each one credibly.',\\n    attachmentIds: [\\n      '0d232466-6bcb-4b15-ab99-604b1bb01526',\\n      '2028d990-7e6a-4ad1-9b37-60ed5ac27a25',\\n      '33968e28-329f-49da-8d2e-3d516a0e3b40',\\n    ],\\n  }),\\n]) as [string, string];\\nsetActivity('Offering to organize your trip');\\ndisplay(\\n  <Stack gap={2}>\\n    <Paragraph>\\n      I've read through everything — here's what I can see you're juggling:\\n    </Paragraph>\\n    <List items={[\\n      'A markdown notes file with the full Tanzania itinerary — Cairo stopover, Arusha, Ngorongoro, Zanzibar, dates, contacts, packing lists.',\\n      'A spreadsheet with two sheets: a detailed cost breakdown across every leg of the trip, plus what looks like a safari balance summary.',\\n      'The official Ngorongoro Conservation Area tariffs PDF — entry fees, crater service fees, vehicle fees, all the line items.',\\n      'A gorgeous Stone Town photo — that courtyard with the whitewashed balconies and carved doors.',\\n      'Your voice memo from the crater rim — the bracelets for Athina Mari, Emmanuel the driver, and the ranger tip nobody warned you about.',\\n    ]} />\\n    <Paragraph>\\n      That's a lot to keep straight on a phone, and there are real things here you don't want to lose track of — the unrecorded bracelet cost, that extra ranger tip, the photo, Richard's contact, the balance still due on the safari.\\n    </Paragraph>\\n    <Paragraph>\\n      Want me to pull all of this together into one organized place you can open and check — pages for your itinerary, costs, park fees, and notes, with everything from every file in one spot? I won't drop anything.\\n    </Paragraph>\\n  </Stack>\\n);\\nsetActivity('Organizing your Tanzania trip');\\n// The user said yes to organizing their supplied material — run the organizer tasklist.\\n// This builds all per-topic specialist spaces AND the live app over the data in one workflow.\\n// Pass every attachment id so the builder reads the source itself, plus the image/audio facts that only vision & transcription could extract.\\nawait tasklist('organize_material', {\\n  request: 'Organize all the supplied Tanzania trip material into an app. The trip spans Cairo (Aug 3-5), Arusha, Ngorongoro Crater, and Zanzibar/Stone Town, traveling as Vasilis + Athina Mari. Build: an itinerary page, a costs/tracker page, a park-fees reference, and a notes/memories page. Seed all data from the files. Include these image- and audio-only facts the builder cannot re-read: the Stone Town photo (a courtyard between whitewashed buildings with carved wooden balconies and ornate doors — the user loved it and wants to keep it); a voice memo from the crater rim recording that the user bought two beaded bracelets for Athina Mari from a Maasai lady at the rim for ~$20-25 (~TZS 35,000 cash); the driver-guide at the crater was Emmanuel (not Richard from the office) who was excellent; Emmanuel mentioned an expectation of a ~TZS 5,000 extra ranger tip at the gate, separate from park fees, in cash — the user wants to remember to ask Richard about this before the safari balance payment.',\\n  sourceSummary: 'A markdown notes file with the full Tanzania itinerary (Cairo stopover, Arusha, Ngorongoro, Zanzibar dates/contacts/packing lists), a spreadsheet with detailed costs across every leg plus a safari balance summary, the official Ngorongoro Conservation Area tariffs PDF with all fee categories, a Stone Town photo, and a voice memo from the crater rim with personal notes about purchases, the driver, and an unexpected ranger tip.',\\n  attachmentIds: [\\n    '0d232466-6bcb-4b15-ab99-604b1bb01526',\\n    '2028d990-7e6a-4ad1-9b37-60ed5ac27a25',\\n    '33968e28-329f-49da-8d2e-3d516a0e3b40',\\n    '6a5d9f14-644b-4698-a341-109093144d31',\\n    // Voice memo — only transcription exists (already in the user's message), no separate file id.\\n  ],\\n  specialistFacts: `Voice memo from Ngorongoro crater rim:\\n- Bought two beaded bracelets for Athina Mari from a Maasai lady at the rim. Paid ~TZS 35,000 cash (~$20-25), exact amount unrecorded.\\n- Driver-guide for the crater day was Emmanuel (not Richard). Excellent — pointed out wildlife before they saw it.\\n- Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip expected at the gate: ~TZS 5,000 cash, separate from park fees. Nobody told them beforehand.\\n- User wants to ask Richard (office contact) about this ranger tip before the safari balance payment.\\n\\nPhoto (Stone Town, Zanzibar):\\n- An open-air courtyard between tall white-painted buildings in ornate Middle Eastern / Mediterranean style.\\n- Multiple stacked wooden balconies, carved wooden doors, dappled light. The user loves this shot — it captured the atmosphere of Stone Town.`,\\n}).then((organized) => display(\\n  organized.ok\\n    ? (\\n      <Stack gap={2}>\\n        <Callout variant=\\\"success\\\" title=\\\"All done — your trip is organized\\\">\\n          Everything from your notes, spreadsheet, park-fee PDF, Stone Town photo, and crater voice memo is now in one place, with pages for your itinerary, costs, park fees, and notes.\\n        </Callout>\\n        <Paragraph>Open your project and you'll find an app ready to go — every leg, every cost, the Ngorongoro tariffs, the bracelets, Emmanuel's ranger-tip heads-up, and your Stone Town photo, all together. No more digging through files on your phone.</Paragraph>\\n      </Stack>\\n    )\\n    : (\\n      <Stack gap={2}>\\n        <Callout variant=\\\"warning\\\" title=\\\"Mostly organized — a couple of pieces need a second look\\\">\\n          I got everything pulled together, but a part of the setup didn't complete cleanly. The core structure is there — let me know what's missing and I'll finish it.\\n        </Callout>\\n        {organized.reason && <Paragraph>{organized.reason}</Paragraph>}\\n      </Stack>\\n    )\\n));\",\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-2026-itinerary/tasklists/research_and_store/02-store.md:17:const w = writeKnowledge('tanzania-trip','cairo-stopover', slug, String(research.answer), { source: 'researched' });\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/.data/pages-build/entry.tsx:3:import Page0 from \"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/pages/index.tsx\";\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/.data/pages-build/entry.tsx:4:import Page1 from \"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/pages/itinerary.tsx\";\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/.data/pages-build/entry.tsx:5:import Page2 from \"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/pages/notes-memories.t