rows: at\nleast one read endpoint per view the app shows. Each `route` encodes its HTTP method LAST (e.g.\n`items-list/GET`, `item-detail/[id]/GET`, `item-create/POST`); methods are GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE.\nName the tables each endpoint touches so the implement step can query real columns. Emit one statement:\n\n```typescript\ncurrentTask.resolve({\n  endpoints: [\n    {\n      route: '<name>/GET',\n      purpose: '<what it returns or does>',\n      tables: [ '<table name from plan_tables.tables it reads/writes>' ],\n    },\n  ],\n});\n```\n","numLines":28,"startLine":1,"totalLines":28}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_LCsQac8bkhcNhXzJaChjDyUC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: implement_endpoints\n3\toutput:\n4\t  route: string\n5\t  name: string\n6\t  ok: boolean\n7\tdependsOn: [plan_endpoints, plan_tables, implement_tables]\n8\tforEach: plan_endpoints.endpoints\n9\trole: general\n10\tfunctions: []\n11\t---\n12\t\n13\tWrite ONE typed API handler into the LIVE project's `api/`. Your endpoint is in `item` =\n14\t{ route, purpose, tables }, where `route` already encodes the method last (e.g. `items-list/GET`).\n15\t`plan_tables.tables` (the real schemas being written) is in scope — read its columns so your query and\n16\t`Output` type match real data. Write the FULL endpoint ESM module inline with the array-`join(\"\\n\")`\n17\tpattern (real line breaks): it MUST export a UNIQUE string `name` (the stable id the page passes to\n18\t`useApi` — without it the loader rejects the whole app), a `description`, an `Input` interface, an\n19\t`Output` interface, and a default `async (input, ctx) => Output` handler that reads/writes through\n20\t`ctx.db` (`await ctx.db.query/insert/update/remove`). `writeProjectApi` returns `{ ok, error? }` and\n21\tvalidates the module at write time; rewrite and retry if `w.ok` is false. Emit one statement:\n22\t\n23\t```typescript\n24\tconst ep = item;\n25\tconst name = ep.route.split('/')[0].replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]+/g, '');\n26\tconst table = Array.isArray(ep.tables) && ep.tables[0] ? ep.tables[0] : (plan_tables.tables[0] ? plan_tables.tables[0].name : 'items');\n27\tconst src = [\n28\t  \"export const name = '\" + name + \"';\",\n29\t  \"export const description = '\" + String(ep.purpose).replace(/'/g, '') + \"';\",\n30\t  \"export interface Input {}\",\n31\t  \"export interface Output { items: any[] }\",\n32\t  \"export default async function handler(_input: Input, ctx: { db: any }): Promise<Output> {\",\n33\t  \"  const items = await ctx.db.query('\" + table + \"');\",\n34\t  \"  return { items };\",\n35\t  \"}\",\n36\t].join(\"\\n\");\n37\tconst w = writeProjectApi(ep.route, src);\n38\tcurrentTask.resolve({ route: ep.route, name, ok: w.ok });\n39\t```\n40\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4abecf79-4263-4bbb-a5c4-a77231683cc7","uuid":"214ec66f-e72f-461d-b966-eb051f10a556","timestamp":"2026-07-16T15:16:13.407Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/06-implement_endpoints.md","content":"---\nid: implement_endpoints\noutput:\n  route: string\n  name: string\n  ok: boolean\ndependsOn: [plan_endpoints, plan_tables, implement_tables]\nforEach: plan_endpoints.endpoints\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nWrite ONE typed API handler into the LIVE project's `api/`. Your endpoint is in `item` =\n{ route, purpose, tables }, where `route` already encodes the method last (e.g. `items-list/GET`).\n`plan_tables.tables` (the real schemas being written) is in scope — read its columns so your query and\n`Output` type match real data. Write the FULL endpoint ESM module inline with the array-`join(\"\\n\")`\npattern (real line breaks): it MUST export a UNIQUE string `name` (the stable id the page passes to\n`useApi` — without it the loader rejects the whole app), a `description`, an `Input` interface, an\n`Output` interface, and a default `async (input, ctx) => Output` handler that reads/writes through\n`ctx.db` (`await ctx.db.query/insert/update/remove`). `writeProjectApi` returns `{ ok, error? }` and\nvalidates the module at write time; rewrite and retry if `w.ok` is false. Emit one statement:\n\n```typescript\nconst ep = item;\nconst name = ep.route.split('/')[0].replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]+/g, '');\nconst table = Array.isArray(ep.tables) && ep.tables[0] ? ep.tables[0] : (plan_tables.tables[0] ? plan_tables.tables[0].name : 'items');\nconst src = [\n  \"export const name = '\" + name + \"';\",\n  \"export const description = '\" + String(ep.purpose).replace(/'/g, '') + \"';\",\n  \"export interface Input {}\",\n  \"export interface Output { items: any[] }\",\n  \"export default async function handler(_input: Input, ctx: { db: any }): Promise<Output> {\",\n  \"  const items = await ctx.db.query('\" + table + \"');\",\n  \"  return { items };\",\n  \"}\",\n].join(\"\\n\");\nconst w = writeProjectApi(ep.route, src);\ncurrentTask.resolve({ route: ep.route, name, ok: w.ok });\n```\n","numLines":40,"startLine":1,"totalLines":40}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_4ws649RmKx3cQYKGKkQjnlho","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tinput:\n3\t  query: string\n4\t  attachmentIds: array\n5\t---\n6\t\n7\tBuild a complete, openable live-project app from supplied material — as a PLAN → per-item BUILD\n8\tpipeline, so no single model turn has to author a whole app at once. First read the attachments, then\n9\tmake a holistic plan of the app (its tables, endpoints, reusable components, and MULTIPLE pages). From\n10\tthere each category is a `plan → implement` pair that the host fans out one file at a time: plan the\n11\ttables → write each table (with its source-derived rows), plan the endpoints → write each typed API,\n12\tplan the components → write each reusable component, plan the pages → write each page (which imports\n13\tthe components and reads the endpoints). A final node writes the persistent chat layout and reports\n14\twhat was built. Every write is its own bounded node, so a slip on one file no longer loses the build;\n15\teach writer returns `{ ok, error? }` and validates at write time. Pages use `@app/runtime` data hooks\n16\tand `@lmthing/css` design tokens only.\n17\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4abecf79-4263-4bbb-a5c4-a77231683cc7","uuid":"47bd03f5-f57d-4199-a136-8be6d7a7da2e","timestamp":"2026-07-16T15:16:13.407Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/index.md","content":"---\ninput:\n  query: string\n  attachmentIds: array\n---\n\nBuild a complete, openable live-project app from supplied material — as a PLAN → per-item BUILD\npipeline, so no single model turn has to author a whole app at once. First read the attachments, then\nmake a holistic plan of the app (its tables, endpoints, reusable components, and MULTIPLE pages). From\nthere each category is a `plan → implement` pair that the host fans out one file at a time: plan the\ntables → write each table (with its source-derived rows), plan the endpoints → write each typed API,\nplan the components → write each reusable component, plan the pages → write each page (which imports\nthe components and reads the endpoints). A final node writes the persistent chat layout and reports\nwhat was built. Every write is its own bounded node, so a slip on one file no longer loses the build;\neach writer returns `{ ok, error? }` and validates at write time. Pages use `@app/runtime` data hooks\nand `@lmthing/css` design tokens only.\n","numLines":17,"startLine":1,"totalLines":17}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_bWoGqiyTYij9oWAmGom2Ii6j","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: implement_pages\n3\toutput:\n4\t  route: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [plan_pages, plan_endpoints, plan_components, implement_components]\n7\tforEach: plan_pages.pages\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite ONE React page into the LIVE project's `pages/`. Your page is in `item` =\n13\t{ route, purpose, endpoints, components } (`index` is the home; `items/[id]` is a dynamic route).\n14\t`plan_endpoints.endpoints` and `plan_components.components` are in scope. Write the FULL `.tsx` source\n15\tinline with the array-`join(\"\\n\")` pattern (real line breaks).\n16\t\n17\tWiring rules — the app fails to compile if you break them:\n18\t- Import data hooks ONLY from `@app/runtime` (`useApi`/`useApiMutation`/`apiCall`/`Link`/`useParams`) —\n19\t  never `fetch` a raw URL, and NEVER import `react-router`, `@radix-ui/*`, `@agent-chat/react`, or a\n20\t  relative `use-api`; none exist in a generated project.\n21\t- Read data by passing an endpoint's logical `name` to `useApi` (the same id the endpoint exported).\n22\t- IMPORT the reusable components you planned, by relative path from `pages/` to `components/`: a\n23\t  top-level page uses `../components/<Name>`, a page one directory deep uses `../../components/<Name>`.\n24\t- STYLE WITH `@lmthing/css` DESIGN TOKENS ONLY (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted`,\n25\t  `border-border`) — never a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a stock Tailwind color.\n26\t\n27\t`writeProjectPage` validates the page has a default export and parses, returning `{ ok, error? }`;\n28\trewrite and retry if `w.ok` is false. Emit one statement:\n29\t\n30\t```typescript\n31\tconst pg = item;\n32\tconst depth = String(pg.route).split('/').length; // 'index' → 1, 'items/[id]' → 2\n33\tconst up = '../'.repeat(depth);                    // '../' to reach the project root from this 