{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_FtD0aTjk2fZITOm8OgREqMEB","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_components\n3\toutput:\n4\t  components: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, plan_endpoints]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tPlan the REUSABLE components the pages will share — the point is UI written ONCE and imported by\n11\tseveral pages, not per-page markup. `query`, `plan_app` (`plan_app.components`), and `plan_endpoints`\n12\t(`plan_endpoints.endpoints`) are in scope. This is a THINKING step — no writers. Plan a small set of\n13\tpresentational components (a `Card`, a `Row`, a `Badge`, a `StatTile`, an `EmptyState`) that render one\n14\trecord or one value and will appear on more than one page. Each `name` is PascalCase; state the `props`\n15\tit takes so the implement step and the pages agree on the shape. Emit one statement:\n16\t\n17\t```typescript\n18\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n19\t  components: [\n20\t    {\n21\t      name: '<ComponentName>',\n22\t      purpose: '<the repeated UI it renders, and which pages use it>',\n23\t      props: [ '<propName: type>' ],\n24\t    },\n25\t  ],\n26\t});\n27\t```\n28\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4abecf79-4263-4bbb-a5c4-a77231683cc7","uuid":"87f3dce5-3ec2-4bf3-9af0-32b21df3958d","timestamp":"2026-07-16T15:33:34.104Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/07-plan_components.md","content":"---\nid: plan_components\noutput:\n  components: array\ndependsOn: [plan_app, plan_endpoints]\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nPlan the REUSABLE components the pages will share — the point is UI written ONCE and imported by\nseveral pages, not per-page markup. `query`, `plan_app` (`plan_app.components`), and `plan_endpoints`\n(`plan_endpoints.endpoints`) are in scope. This is a THINKING step — no writers. Plan a small set of\npresentational components (a `Card`, a `Row`, a `Badge`, a `StatTile`, an `EmptyState`) that render one\nrecord or one value and will appear on more than one page. Each `name` is PascalCase; state the `props`\nit takes so the implement step and the pages agree on the shape. Emit one statement:\n\n```typescript\ncurrentTask.resolve({\n  components: [\n    {\n      name: '<ComponentName>',\n      purpose: '<the repeated UI it renders, and which pages use it>',\n      props: [ '<propName: type>' ],\n    },\n  ],\n});\n```\n","numLines":28,"startLine":1,"totalLines":28}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_DVsy0NK7oU69bQbyOVMSiVeA","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: implement_components\n3\toutput:\n4\t  name: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [plan_components]\n7\tforEach: plan_components.components\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite ONE reusable component into the LIVE project's `components/`. Your component is in `item` =\n13\t{ name, purpose, props }. Call `writeProjectComponent(item.name, src)` — the name MUST be PascalCase\n14\tand the source MUST have a DEFAULT export (the component a page renders); the writer validates both and\n15\tthat it parses as TSX, returning `{ ok, error? }`. Write the FULL `.tsx` source inline with the\n16\tarray-`join(\"\\n\")` pattern. This is presentational UI: take the record/value via props and render it —\n17\tdo NOT fetch data here (pages pass data in). STYLE WITH `@lmthing/css` DESIGN TOKENS ONLY (`bg-card`,\n18\t`text-foreground`, `text-muted`, `border-border`, `bg-primary`) — never a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a\n19\tstock Tailwind color (`gray-500`, `blue-600`). Import only from `react`/`@app/runtime` if needed. Emit\n20\tone statement:\n21\t\n22\t```typescript\n23\tconst c = item;\n24\tconst src = [\n25\t  \"export default function \" + c.name + \"({ title, subtitle }: { title: string; subtitle?: string }) {\",\n26\t  \"  return (\",\n27\t  \"    <div className=\\\"rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-3\\\">\",\n28\t  \"      <p className=\\\"font-medium text-foreground\\\">{title}</p>\",\n29\t  \"      {subtitle ? <p className=\\\"text-sm text-muted\\\">{subtitle}</p> : null}\",\n30\t  \"    </div>\",\n31\t  \"  );\",\n32\t  \"}\",\n33\t].join(\"\\n\");\n34\tconst w = writeProjectComponent(c.name, src);\n35\tcurrentTask.resolve({ name: c.name, ok: w.ok });\n36\t```\n37\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4abecf79-4263-4bbb-a5c4-a77231683cc7","uuid":"bd6a56b6-16f3-4606-8c4d-06791cbce63a","timestamp":"2026-07-16T15:33:34.105Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/08-implement_components.md","content":"---\nid: implement_components\noutput:\n  name: string\n  ok: boolean\ndependsOn: [plan_components]\nforEach: plan_components.components\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nWrite ONE reusable component into the LIVE project's `components/`. Your component is in `item` =\n{ name, purpose, props }. Call `writeProjectComponent(item.name, src)` — the name MUST be PascalCase\nand the source MUST have a DEFAULT export (the component a page renders); the writer validates both and\nthat it parses as TSX, returning `{ ok, error? }`. Write the FULL `.tsx` source inline with the\narray-`join(\"\\n\")` pattern. This is presentational UI: take the record/value via props and render it —\ndo NOT fetch data here (pages pass data in). STYLE WITH `@lmthing/css` DESIGN TOKENS ONLY (`bg-card`,\n`text-foreground`, `text-muted`, `border-border`, `bg-primary`) — never a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a\nstock Tailwind color (`gray-500`, `blue-600`). Import only from `react`/`@app/runtime` if needed. Emit\none statement:\n\n```typescript\nconst c = item;\nconst src = [\n  \"export default function \" + c.name + \"({ title, subtitle }: { title: string; subtitle?: string }) {\",\n  \"  return (\",\n  \"    <div className=\\\"rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-3\\\">\",\n  \"      <p className=\\\"font-medium text-foreground\\\">{title}</p>\",\n  \"      {subtitle ? <p className=\\\"text-sm text-muted\\\">{subtitle}</p> : null}\",\n  \"    </div>\",\n  \"  );\",\n  \"}\",\n].join(\"\\n\");\nconst w = writeProjectComponent(c.name, src);\ncurrentTask.resolve({ name: c.name, ok: w.ok });\n```\n","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_UCKVEaj1qeHGkDJwLX75RBD5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# File formats\n2\t\n3\tThe exact on-disk shapes each authoring global writes.\n4\t\n5\t## Table schema — `writeTableSchema(name, schema)` → `database/<name>.json`\n6\t\n7\t`name` is a lowercase slug. `schema` is an object:\n8\t\n9\t```json\n10\t{\n11\t  \"title\": \"Feed items\",\n12\t  \"description\": \"One personalized item in the user's feed.\",\n13\t  \"columns\": {\n14\t    \"id\":        { \"type\": \"string\",  \"description\": \"unique id\", \"primaryKey\": true, \"generated\": \"uuid\" },\n15\t    \"title\":     { \"type\": \"string\",  \"description\": \"headline\", \"required\": true },\n16\t    \"url\":       { \"type\": \"string\",  \"description\": \"source URL\", \"required\": true, \"unique\": true },\n17\t    \"score\":     { \"type\": \"number\",  \"description\": \"relevance rank\", \"default\": 0 },\n18\t    \"read\":      { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"description\": \"opened yet\", \"default\": false },\n19\t    \"createdAt\": { \"type\": \"date\",    \"description\": \"when it entered the feed\", \"generated\": \"now\" }\n20\t  },\n21\t  \"relations\": {\n22\t    \"comments\": { \"hasMany\": \"comments\", \"via\": \"feedItemId\", \"description\": \"notes attached\" }\n23\t  }\n24\t}\n25\t```\n26\t\n27\t- Column `type`: `string` | `number` | `boolean` | `date` | `json`.\n28\t- Exactly one column sets `primaryKey: true` (use `generated: \"uuid\"`). `generated` is `uuid`|`now`.\n29\t- `references`: `{ table, column?, onDelete? }` (`onDelete`: `cascade`|`setNull`|`restrict`) is a\n30\t  real SQLite foreign key.\n31\t- Relations: `belongsTo` (this table holds the FK, `via` = its column) or `hasMany` (target holds\n32\t  the FK back). Both need a `description`. Validation fails loud on any missing description.\n33\t\n34\t## API handler — `writeApi('<name>/<METHOD>', src)` → `api/<name>/<METHOD>.ts`\n35\t\n36\tThe route's LAST segment is the HTTP method (`GET`|`POST`|`PUT`|`PATCH`|`DELETE`); the rest is the\n37\tendpoint path. `src` is a full ESM handler module:\n38\t\n39\t```ts\n40\texport const name = 'items-list';\n41\texport const description = 'List all items, newest first.';\n42\texport interface Input {}\n43\texport interface Output { items: { id: string; title: string }[] }\n44\texport default async function handler(input: Input, ctx: { db: any }): Promise<Output> {\n45\t  const items = await ctx.db.query('items', { orderBy: { column: 'createdAt', dir: 'desc' } });\n46\t  return { items };\n47\t}\n48\t```\n49\t\n50\t`ctx.db` is the async data API: `await ctx.db.query/insert/update/remove/tables(...)`. `Input`/\n51\t`Output` become the endpoint's JSON-Schema contract. `import { HttpError } from '@app/runtime'` to\n52\tsignal 4xx/5xx.\n53\t\n54\t## Page — `writePage(route, src)` → `pages/<route>.tsx`\n55\t\n56\t`route` is `index` (root) or a path like `items/[id]` (a `[seg]` is dynamic, read via\n57\t`useParams`). `src` is a full `.tsx` module with a default-exported component. Data hooks come from\n58\t`@app/runtime`: `useApi(name, input?, opts?)` (GET/DELETE reads → `{ data, error, isLoading,\n59\trefetch }`), `useApiMutation(name, { invalidates? })` (POST/PATCH/PUT → `{ mutate }`), `apiCall`,\n60\t`Link`, `navigate`. Style with design tokens ONLY.\n61\t\n62\t## Hook — `writeHook(slug, src)` → `hooks/<slug>.ts`\n63\t\n64\tDefault export is one of:\n65\t\n66\t```ts\n67\t// cron — time-based\n68\texport default { type: 'cron', every: '30m', trigger: 'space/agent#action' };\n69\t// database — write-triggered (declarative)\n70\texport default { type: 'database', on: { table: 'raw_items', event: 'insert' }, trigger: 'space/agent#action' };\n71\t// database — imperative\n72\texport default {\n73\t  type: 'database', on: { table: 'raw_items', event: 'insert' },\n74\t  handler: async ({ row, db, delegate }) => { /* ... */ },\n75\t};\n76\t```\n77\t\n78\t`every` is `<n>m|h|d` (mutually exclusive with `daily: 'HH:MM'`). A database hook's `event` is\n79\t`insert`|`update`|`remove`, and it has EXACTLY ONE of `trigger` / `handler`.\n80\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4abecf79-4263-4bbb-a5c4-a77231683cc7","uuid":"677eace8-34f2-4e97-b6a6-b07d20110a77","timestamp":"2026-07-16T15:33:34.106Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/knowledge/app_building/model/file-formats.md","content":"# File formats\n\nThe exact on-disk shapes each authoring global writes.\n\n## Table schema — `writeTableSchema(name, schema)` → `database/<name>.json`\n\n`name` is a lowercase slug. `schema` is an object:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Feed items\",\n  \"description\": \"One personalized item in the user's feed.\",\n  \"columns\": {\n    \"id\":        { \"type\": \"string\",  \"description\": \"unique id\", \"primaryKey\": true, \"generated\": \"uuid\" },\n    \"title\":     { \"type\": \"string\",  \"description\": \"headline\", \"required\": true },\n    \"url\":       { \"type\": \"string\",  \"description\": \"source URL\", \"required\": true, \"unique\": true },\n    \"score\":     { \"type\": \"number\",  \"description\": \"relevance rank\", \"default\": 0 },\n    \"read\":      { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"description\": \"opened yet\", \"default\": false },\n    \"createdAt\": { \"type\": \"date\",    \"description\": \"when it entered the feed\", \"generated\": \"now\" }\n  },\n  \"relations\": {\n    \"comments\": { \"hasMany\": \"comments\", \"via\": \"feedItemId\", \"description\": \"notes attached\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- Column `type`: `string` | `number` | `boolean` | `date` | `json`.\n- Exactly one column sets `primaryKey: true` (use `generated: \"uuid\"`). `generated` is `uuid`|`now`.\n- `references`: `{ table, column?, onDelete? }` (`onDelete`: `cascade`|`setNull`|`restrict`) is a\n  real SQLite foreign key.\n- Relations: `belongsTo` (this table holds the FK, `via` = its column) or `hasMany` (target holds\n  the FK back). Both need a `description`. Validation fails loud on any missing description.\n\n## API handler — `writeApi('<name>/<METHOD>', src)` → `api/<name>/<METHOD>.ts`\n\nThe route's LAST segment is the HTTP method (`GET`|`POST`|`PUT`|`PATCH`|`DELETE`); the rest is the\nendpoint path. `src` is a full ESM handler module:\n\n```ts\nexport const name = 'items-list';\nexport const description = 'List all items, newest first.';\nexport interface Input {}\nexport interface Output { items: { id: string; title: string }[] }\nexport default async function handler(input: Input, ctx: { db: any }): Promise<Output> {\n  const items = await ctx.db.query('items', { orderBy: { column: 'createdAt', dir: 'desc' } });\n  return { items };\n}\n```\n\n`ctx.db` is the async data API: `await ctx.db.query/insert/update/remove/tables(...)`. `Input`/\n`Output` become the endpoint's JSON-Schema contract. `import { HttpError } from '@app/runtime'` to\nsignal 4xx/5xx.\n\n## Page — `writePage(route, src)` → `pages/<route>.tsx`\n\n`route` is `index` (root) or a path like `items/[id]` (a `[seg]` is dynamic, read via\n`useParams`). `src` is a full `.tsx` module with a default-exported component. Data hooks come from\n`@app/runtime`: `useApi(name, input?, opts?)` (GET/DELETE reads → `{ data, error, isLoading,\nrefetch }`), `useApiMutation(name, { invalidates? })` (POST/PATCH/PUT → `{ mutate }`), `apiCall`,\n`Link`, `navigate`. Style with design tokens ONLY.\n\n## Hook — `writeHook(slug, src)` → `hooks/<slug>.ts`\n\nDefault export is one of:\n\n```ts\n// cron — time-based\nexport default { type: 'cron', every: '30m', trigger: 'space/agent#action' };\n// database — write-triggered (declarative)\nexport default { type: 'database', on: { table: 'raw_items', event: 'insert' }, trigger: 'space/agent#action' };\n// database — imperative\nexport default {\n  type: 'database', on: { table: 'raw_items', event: 'insert' },\n  handler: async ({ row, db, delegate }) => { /* ... */ },\n};\n```\n\n`every` is `<n>m|h|d` (mutually exclusive with `daily: 'HH:MM'`). A database hook's `event` is\n`insert`|`update`|`remove`, and it has EXACTLY ONE of `trigger` / `handler`.\n","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":80}}}
