{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_Ae8garOStjwtawx8832AqnoY","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_app\n3\toutput:\n4\t  title: string\n5\t  purpose: string\n6\t  tables: array\n7\t  endpoints: array\n8\t  components: array\n9\t  pages: array\n10\tdependsOn: [read_sources]\n11\trole: general\n12\tfunctions: []\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\tDesign the WHOLE app holistically before any file is written. `query` and `read_sources` (the\n16\tsource-derived build brief in `read_sources.summary`) are in scope. This is the THINKING step: reason\n17\tfrom the material into a concrete shape, then resolve the plan object. You have no file writers here —\n18\tjust produce the high-level lists that the per-category planners below will refine.\n19\t\n20\tSubstitute REAL values derived from the material for every `<…>` (never leave a placeholder). Plan for\n21\tan app the user OPENS: enough tables to hold every kind of record the source contains, endpoints to\n22\tread them, a few REUSABLE components (a card, a row, a stat) that repeat across pages, and MULTIPLE\n23\tpages — an `index` home plus the list/detail/dashboard views the material calls for. Emit one\n24\tstatement:\n25\t\n26\t```typescript\n27\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n28\t  title: '<human-readable app title>',\n29\t  purpose: '<one sentence: what the user opens this app to do>',\n30\t  // High-level only; plan_tables refines schemas + rows.\n31\t  tables: [ { name: '<table_slug>', purpose: '<what it stores, from the source>' } ],\n32\t  // Each route encodes its HTTP method last, e.g. 'items-list/GET'. Methods: GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE.\n33\t  endpoints: [ { route: '<name>/GET', purpose: '<what it returns or does>' } ],\n34\t  // Reusable UI the pages share — a card/row/badge/stat, PascalCase name.\n35\t  components: [ { name: '<ComponentName>', purpose: '<the repeated UI it renders>' } ],\n36\t  // Use 'index' for the home; add list/detail/dashboard pages the material needs.\n37\t  pages: [ { route: 'index', purpose: '<what the home shows>' } ],\n38\t});\n39\t```\n40\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4abecf79-4263-4bbb-a5c4-a77231683cc7","uuid":"4b73e388-4bac-4782-88cd-bdc9ee7c2089","timestamp":"2026-07-16T15:46:47.905Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/02-plan_app.md","content":"---\nid: plan_app\noutput:\n  title: string\n  purpose: string\n  tables: array\n  endpoints: array\n  components: array\n  pages: array\ndependsOn: [read_sources]\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nDesign the WHOLE app holistically before any file is written. `query` and `read_sources` (the\nsource-derived build brief in `read_sources.summary`) are in scope. This is the THINKING step: reason\nfrom the material into a concrete shape, then resolve the plan object. You have no file writers here —\njust produce the high-level lists that the per-category planners below will refine.\n\nSubstitute REAL values derived from the material for every `<…>` (never leave a placeholder). Plan for\nan app the user OPENS: enough tables to hold every kind of record the source contains, endpoints to\nread them, a few REUSABLE components (a card, a row, a stat) that repeat across pages, and MULTIPLE\npages — an `index` home plus the list/detail/dashboard views the material calls for. Emit one\nstatement:\n\n```typescript\ncurrentTask.resolve({\n  title: '<human-readable app title>',\n  purpose: '<one sentence: what the user opens this app to do>',\n  // High-level only; plan_tables refines schemas + rows.\n  tables: [ { name: '<table_slug>', purpose: '<what it stores, from the source>' } ],\n  // Each route encodes its HTTP method last, e.g. 'items-list/GET'. Methods: GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE.\n  endpoints: [ { route: '<name>/GET', purpose: '<what it returns or does>' } ],\n  // Reusable UI the pages share — a card/row/badge/stat, PascalCase name.\n  components: [ { name: '<ComponentName>', purpose: '<the repeated UI it renders>' } ],\n  // Use 'index' for the home; add list/detail/dashboard pages the material needs.\n  pages: [ { route: 'index', purpose: '<what the home shows>' } ],\n});\n```\n","numLines":40,"startLine":1,"totalLines":40}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_9GVvyf5TDLGQFfji5Sb7ucrk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_tables\n3\toutput:\n4\t  tables: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, read_sources]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tTurn the holistic table list into a DETAILED, source-grounded data model. `query`, `read_sources`\n11\t(the build brief), and `plan_app` (`plan_app.tables` is the high-level list) are in scope. This is\n12\tstill a THINKING step — no writers here. For every table produce its full `schema` AND the actual\n13\t`rows` read from the material, so the implement step can seed data at creation. Do NOT invent rows: use\n14\tonly values the source states (identifiers, contacts, dates, payments, stated totals, attribution). If\n15\tthe source has no rows for a table, drop that table — a created-but-empty table is the #1 failure.\n16\t\n17\tEvery table schema needs a `title`, a `description`, and `columns` where each column has a\n18\t`description` and exactly one uuid primary key. Keys in each row object MUST match the column names.\n19\tEmit one statement:\n20\t\n21\t```typescript\n22\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n23\t  tables: [\n24\t    {\n25\t      name: '<source-derived table name>',\n26\t      schema: {\n27\t        title: '<Title>',\n28\t        description: '<what this table stores>',\n29\t        columns: {\n30\t          id: { type: 'string', description: 'Primary key', primaryKey: true, generated: 'uuid' },\n31\t          // …one column per field the record carries, each with a real description.\n32\t        },\n33\t      },\n34\t      // One object per record READ FROM THE MATERIAL. Never carry over an example value.\n35\t      rows: [ /* { id: '…', …source-derived fields } */ ],\n36\t    },\n37\t  ],\n38\t});\n39\t```\n40\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4abecf79-4263-4bbb-a5c4-a77231683cc7","uuid":"df74478b-a5fd-4afa-98b2-3bf8f0a2432b","timestamp":"2026-07-16T15:46:47.906Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/03-plan_tables.md","content":"---\nid: plan_tables\noutput:\n  tables: array\ndependsOn: [plan_app, read_sources]\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nTurn the holistic table list into a DETAILED, source-grounded data model. `query`, `read_sources`\n(the build brief), and `plan_app` (`plan_app.tables` is the high-level list) are in scope. This is\nstill a THINKING step — no writers here. For every table produce its full `schema` AND the actual\n`rows` read from the material, so the implement step can seed data at creation. Do NOT invent rows: use\nonly values the source states (identifiers, contacts, dates, payments, stated totals, attribution). If\nthe source has no rows for a table, drop that table — a created-but-empty table is the #1 failure.\n\nEvery table schema needs a `title`, a `description`, and `columns` where each column has a\n`description` and exactly one uuid primary key. Keys in each row object MUST match the column names.\nEmit one statement:\n\n```typescript\ncurrentTask.resolve({\n  tables: [\n    {\n      name: '<source-derived table name>',\n      schema: {\n        title: '<Title>',\n        description: '<what this table stores>',\n        columns: {\n          id: { type: 'string', description: 'Primary key', primaryKey: true, generated: 'uuid' },\n          // …one column per field the record carries, each with a real description.\n        },\n      },\n      // One object per record READ FROM THE MATERIAL. Never carry over an example value.\n      rows: [ /* { id: '…', …source-derived fields } */ ],\n    },\n  ],\n});\n```\n","numLines":40,"startLine":1,"totalLines":40}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_g7yQljXr56vtYXLKX33xviZY","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: implement_tables\n3\toutput:\n4\t  name: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [plan_tables]\n7\tforEach: plan_tables.tables\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite ONE table's schema + rows into the LIVE project's `database/`. Your table is in `item` =\n13\t{ name, schema, rows }. Call `writeProjectTable(item.name, item.schema, item.rows)` so the source\n14\trecords land as rows at creation — never write an empty table when `item.rows` has data. `writeProjectTable`\n15\tvalidates the schema on write and returns `{ ok, error? }`; if `w.ok` is false, read `w.error` (a\n16\tmissing column description, a bad relation) and fix it before resolving honestly. Emit one statement:\n17\t\n18\t```typescript\n19\tconst t = item;\n20\tconst w = writeProjectTable(t.name, t.schema, Array.isArray(t.rows) ? t.rows : []);\n21\tcurrentTask.resolve({ name: t.name, ok: w.ok });\n22\t```\n23\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4abecf79-4263-4bbb-a5c4-a77231683cc7","uuid":"a357bd20-75ca-48eb-8ca1-98fe88955c42","timestamp":"2026-07-16T15:46:47.907Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/04-implement_tables.md","content":"---\nid: implement_tables\noutput:\n  name: string\n  ok: boolean\ndependsOn: [plan_tables]\nforEach: plan_tables.tables\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nWrite ONE table's schema + rows into the LIVE project's `database/`. Your table is in `item` =\n{ name, schema, rows }. Call `writeProjectTable(item.name, item.schema, item.rows)` so the source\nrecords land as rows at creation — never write an empty table when `item.rows` has data. `writeProjectTable`\nvalidates the schema on write and returns `{ ok, error? }`; if `w.ok` is false, read `w.error` (a\nmissing column description, a bad relation) and fix it before resolving honestly. Emit one statement:\n\n```typescript\nconst t = item;\nconst w = writeProjectTable(t.name, t.schema, Array.isArray(t.rows) ? t.rows : []);\ncurrentTask.resolve({ name: t.name, ok: w.ok });\n```\n","numLines":23,"startLine":1,"totalLines":23}}}
