tem-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\n        \"system-architect/architect/synthesize_and_run\",\n        \"system-appbuilder/automator/build_live_project\"\n      ],\n      \"yieldKinds\": [\n        \"tasklist\",\n        \"readDocument\",\n        \"loadKnowledge\",\n        \"delegate\",\n        \"inspect\",\n        \"registerSpace\"\n      ],\n      \"yieldCount\": 24,\n      \"errors\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"typecheck_error\",\n          \"message\": \"',' expected.; ',' expected.; Cannot find name 'special'.; Expected 5 arguments, but got 7.\",\n          \"statement\": \"// Aspect 2: beach-practicalities\\nconst opt2 = writeKnowledgeOption(design.slug, f.domain, f.field, f.aspects[1],\\n  \\\"# \\\" + f.aspects[1] + \\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\" +\\n  \\\"Zanzibar's beaches — primarily on the east and north coasts — are the classic tropical unwind after a dusty safari. In August (dry season), days are sunny with temperatures around 25–30°C and low humidity, making beach time very comfortable.\\\\n\\\\n\\\" +\\n  \\\"Practicalities for the fully-booked traveler:\\\\n\\\" +\\n  \\\"- **Tides matter enormously**: The east coast (Paje, Jambiani, Dongwe) has extreme tidal swings. At low tide the water recedes hundreds of meters, exposing sea urchins and sharp coral — reef shoes are essential. High tide brings swimmable water right to resort steps. North-coast beaches (Nungwi, Kendwa) have much smaller tidal variation and are swimmable all day.\\\\n\\\" +\\n  \\\"- **Beach vendors (\\\\\\\"beach boys\\\\\\\")**: Persistent salespeople walk the beaches offering excursions, souvenirs, and \\\"special\\\" goods. A firm, polite \\\\\\\"no thank you\\\\\\\" works if you're not interested. Do not engage if you don't intend to buy; even friendly conversation is interpreted as a sales opening.\\\\n\\\" +\\n  \\\"- **Resort amenities**: Most resorts on the east coast are self-contained with pools, restaurants, and security; many offer excursions to snorkeling, dolphin watching, and spice tours. Since your itinerary is fully booked, check with your tour operator whether beach transfers and activities are already arranged or offered as add-ons.\\\\n\\\" +\\n  \\\"- **Swimming safety**: Rip currents exist on the east coast. Swim in designated areas or where others are swimming. North coast (Kendwa in particular) is calmer. Jellyfish are rare in August but possible — ask locally.\\\\n\\\" +\\n  \\\"- **Dress at resorts**: Beachwear is normal at resort pools and beaches. Going topless is illegal in Tanzania. Some resorts tolerate it on private beaches; most do not.\\\\n\\\\n\\\" +\\n  \\\"Source: \\\" + srcUrl\\n);\",\n          \"attempt\": 1\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"eval_error\",\n          \"message\": \"api endpoint rejected (not saved): the name \\\"questions\\\" is already used by api/questions/[id]/PATCH.ts — endpoint names are unique per project. Pick a different `export const name` (or edit that file).\",\n          \"statement\": \"const w = writeProjectApi(ep.route, src);\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"typecheck_error\",\n          \"message\": \"Cannot find name 'envelope'.; Cannot find name 'envelope'.\",\n          \"statement\": \"// The delegation has been executed and `envelope` is now in scope with the automator's result.\\n// Check the outcome and resolve accordingly.\\n\\nconst result = envelope.ok === true && envelope.data?.ok === true;\",\n          \"attempt\": 1\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"typecheck_error\",\n          \"message\": \"Property 'some' does not exist on type '{ ok: boolean; entries: string[]; error?: string | undefined; }'.\",\n          \"statement\": \"// Check that there are pages (not just tables) — an app they can actually open.\\nconst hasAppPages = dirContents.some((entry: any) => entry.path && entry.path.startsWith('pages/'));\",\n          \"attempt\": 1\n        }\n      ],\n      \"nodeCount\": 161,\n      \"tokens\": {\n